<br>
All pets were buffed in the test because when I first got the pets there damage really wasn't that good IMO. However with buffs things change.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Air Pet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Burnout 5, VoG (for the atk boost), Focus, lvl 62 procing fist, Girdle of Magi'kot, Muzzle of Mardu.<br>
<br>
I broke things up by hour because I was in 3 different groups over the 3 hour time period.<br>
<br>
1st pet = 76dps<br>
2nd pet =71 dps<br>
3rd pet = 81dps<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Water Pet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Had all of the above buffs that the Air Pet had. He also had one of the ranger atk buffs for most of the time. Can't remember what it is called off hand.<br>
<br>
1st pet = 91dps<br>
2nd pet = 96dps<br>
<br>
<br>
Also I am begining to wonder if Girdle of Magi'kot has some sorta procing bonus built into it. I coun't about a 11% increase in proc rate with the belt as compared to the pet not having the belt. /shrug<br>
<br>
I know procing is random so could just be lucky rolls. Just seem he has alot more luck with the belt =0).  All test were done against mobs in the PoV wastelands. I have not been able to buff the water pet up enough to get him to 100dps but I think with the scarecrow buff that enchanters have he might be able to. Dunno, I only know of one enchanter that has the buff on my server, and haven't had a chance to group with him as of late.  Those are my findings, do with it what you will.  Basically we have nothing to fear from beastlords. While there new lvl 64 pet is probably on par with epic in damage, our new pets own theirs, and the air pet tanks very well. <br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
<br>
Also accounted for a 30% resist rate on procs, and spell damage. I always debuff with Malosini so I doubt resist were that high but that seems to be the magic number people use so I did as well.<br>
